description:
&lt;p&gt;Advocacy, &amp; Improvement Senior Manager (FTSU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Play a leading role in responding to Freedom to Speak Up concerns from across the NHS and supporting trust boards to improve their FTSU arrangements, ensuring all NHS workers have a voice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This new role will focus on handling our more complex FTSU casework from across the NHS, working closely with regional colleagues and senior leaders. It will involve directly supporting trust boards to review and improve their FTSU arrangements and leadership behaviours; working closely with the National Guardian’s Office (NGO), the CQC and other key stakeholders; and ensuring alignment of all this with our People Plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll need experience of handling complex and sensitive casework, as well as supporting public sector organisations to improve their systems and culture. In addition, you will need proven skills in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;managing key stakeholder relationships at a senior level, using influence and expertise to drive successful outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;analysing and summarising information, and exercising sound judgement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Max Sheen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Business Support (FTSU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Max.Sheen@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
